                        <aside class="fixed_flex">
                            <h1 class="stroke big">02</h1>
                        </aside>
                        <h3 class="title small">Symptoms</h3>
                        <p>Common symptoms of diarrhea include frequent loose or watery bowel movements, abdominal cramps, bloating, nausea, and sometimes fever. It may also be accompanied by vomiting and dehydration.
                            </p>
                    </article>
                    <article class="padding_2x">
                        <aside class="fixed_flex">
                            <h1 class="stroke big">03</h1>
                        </aside>
                        <h3 class="title small">Treatment</h3>
                        <p>Consuming fluids and electrolytes to prevent dehydration, following a BRAT diet (bananas, rice, applesauce, toast), and using over-the-counter medications like loperamide.
                        </p>
                    </article>
                    <article class="padding_2x">
                        <aside class="fixed_flex">
                            <h1 class="stroke big">04</h1>
                            
                        </aside>
                        <h3 class="title small">Causes</h3>
                        <p>Diarrhea can be caused by various factors such as viral or bacterial infections, food poisoning, consumption of contaminated food or water, certain medications, intestinal disorders, and stress.
                        </p>
                    </article>
